{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id62f34ab9-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5390"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5390"},"text":"§ 5390.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Federal procurement laws and regulations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Regarding construction programs or projects, the Secretary and Indian tribes may negotiate for the inclusion of specific provisions of division B (except sections 1123, 2303, 2304, and 2313) of subtitle I of title 41 and Federal acquisition regulations in any funding agreement entered into under this subchapter. Absent a negotiated agreement, such provisions and regulatory requirements shall not apply.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id62f34aba-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/638/tV/s510"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–638, title V, § 510","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/260/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–260, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-08-18"},"text":"Aug. 18, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/726"},"text":"114 Stat. 726","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id62f34abb-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id62f34abc-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id62f34abd-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s458aaa–9"},"text":"section 458aaa–9 of this title","children":[],"tail":" prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In text, “division B (except sections 1123, 2303, 2304, and 2313) of subtitle I of title 41” substituted for “the Office of Federal Procurement and Policy Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s401"},"text":"41 U.S.C. 401","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)” on authority of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350/s6/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350, § 6(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-04"},"text":"Jan. 4, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/3854"},"text":"124 Stat. 3854","children":[],"tail":", which Act enacted Title 41, Public Contracts."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
